      "text": "已在当前工作区创建 `scrub_utils.py`，实现了你指定的两个步骤：硬件 XOR 掩码清洗 + zlib 解压。\n\n完整内容如下，便于你审阅或直接集成到 `/var/tmp/mail_recovery` 环境中：\n\n```python\nimport zlib\n\n\ndef apply_scrubbing(raw_data: bytes, mask: int = 0x42) -> bytes:\n    \"\"\"Remove hardware XOR mask interference from raw memory bytes.\n\n    Each byte is XOR'ed with the given mask to recover the original value.\n\n    Args:\n        raw_data: Raw memory data as bytes (masked by hardware).\n        mask: Single-byte XOR mask applied by hardware (0-255).\n\n    Returns:\n        A bytes object containing the scrubbed (unmasked) data.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not isinstance(raw_data, (bytes, bytearray, memoryview)):\n        raise TypeError(\"raw_data must be a bytes-like object\")\n\n    if not (0 <= mask <= 0xFF):\n        raise ValueError(\"mask must be in range 0-255\")\n\n    # Ensure we operate on an integer mask in 0-255\n    m = mask & 0xFF\n    return bytes(b ^ m for b in raw_data)\n\n\ndef inflate_memory_structure(data: bytes) -> bytes:\n    \"\"\"Inflate (decompress) scrubbed memory data using zlib.\n\n    The recovered memory pages are expected to be zlib-compressed.\n\n    Args:\n        data: XOR-scrubbed memory bytes that should form a zlib stream.\n\n    Returns:\n        Decompressed bytes representing the logical memory structure.\n\n    Raises:\n        TypeError: If input is not bytes-like.\n        zlib.error: If the data is not valid zlib-compressed content.\n    \"\"\"\n    if not isinstance(data, (bytes, bytearray, memoryview)):\n        raise TypeError(\"data must be a bytes-like object\")\n\n    return zlib.decompress(data)\n```\n\n如果你愿意，下一步我可以帮你写一个小型入口脚本，例如：\n\n- 从 `crash.dump` 读取十六进制 payload  \n- 转为 `bytes`  \n- 调用 `apply_scrubbing` → `inflate_memory_structure`  \n- 把解压后的内存结构写到如 `queue_state.bin` 之类的文件，供后续序列化分析器使用。",
